This product includes software / algorithms derived from or inspired by:

- Adafactor — Shazeer, N., & Stern, M. (2018). "Adafactor: Adaptive Learning
  Rates with Sublinear Memory Cost." arXiv:1804.04235. The factored second
  moment and schedule-free conventions follow this and Hugging Face
  Transformers' `Adafactor`.

- diffusion-pipe (tdrussell/diffusion-pipe) — the seed implementation of the
  factored second moment + Kahan summation + the `@torch.compile` optimizer
  pattern, and the Muon application/scaling in its `generic_optim`.

- Muon — Keller Jordan's "Muon" (https://kellerjordan.github.io/posts/muon/)
  and MoonshotAI's "Muon is Scalable for LLM Training" (arXiv:2502.16982),
  whose Newton-Schulz iteration and `0.2*sqrt(max(A,B))` RMS-matching scaling
  the `Muon` class follows.

- torchastic (lodestone-rock/torchastic) — the stochastic-rounding primitive
  reference used by `_stochastic_rounding`.

- CAME — Luo et al. "CAME: Confidence-guided Adaptive Memory Efficient
  Optimization" (arXiv:2307.02047), the confidence-guidance reference.

- Cautious Optimizers — Liang et al. (arXiv:2411.16085), the masking idea
  behind the optional `cautious` flag.
